Key Match Events: Donovan Mitchell scored a jumper with three-tenths of a second left to give the Cleveland Cavaliers a 114-113 win over the Milwaukee Bucks.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cavaliers are one win away from matching their best start in franchise history, having won their first eight games in 1976-77.
Others: The Bucks played without Khris Middleton, who hasn't yet made his season debut as he recovers from surgery on his ankles.Giannis Antetokounmpo had 34 points, 16 rebounds and nine assists for the Bucks.Damian Lillard had 41 points with nine assists and shot 10 of 15 from 3-point range for the Bucks.
